				\begin{document}$$ \left[\left(p-1\right)*\frac{4^k}{n},p*\frac{4^k}{n}\right] $$\end{document}p−1*4kn,p*4kn for p = 1, …, n, with n equal to the total number of instances. The partial databases created by each CNIDARIA instance can then simply be concatenated to create a full database containing all k-mers.

